<h1 id="Clustering-Algorithms">Clustering Algorithms<a class="anchor-link" href="#Clustering-Algorithms"> </a></h1><p>We'll use the elbow method to find optimal number of clusters. It's an important step in unsupervised algorithm to determine the optimal number of clusters into which the data may be clustered. While KMeans use elbow method, Hierarchical Clustering use dendogram to visualize the optimal number of clusters.</p>
<h2 id="KMeans">KMeans<a class="anchor-link" href="#KMeans"> </a></h2>
</div>
</div>
</div>
    {% raw %}
    
<div class="cell border-box-sizing code_cell rendered">

<div class="output_wrapper">
